                            <comment id="13510944" author="brandon.williams" created="Wed, 5 Dec 2012 23:59:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;First patch renames &apos;ring_id&apos; in peers to &apos;host_id&apos; because that&apos;s what we call it everywhere else including nodetool, so we should be consistent.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Second patch updates the hostid in TMD when it updates the tokens.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13510990" author="tjake" created="Thu, 6 Dec 2012 00:53:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks straight fwd. I can test but this looks like I&apos;ll need to recreate the cluster/system table?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13510992" author="brandon.williams" created="Thu, 6 Dec 2012 00:57:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I tested it and it works, but yeah, you&apos;ll have to wipe out the system table, or I think starting once with -Dcassandra.load_ring=false will work.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
